    <h1>Cal&#xAD;zone ($30 for half, $40 for full)</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200802/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-02"><time>2020-08-02</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>It is too much to or­der this, along with a hefty pizza, even for a ta­ble of five. So I sug­gest you save this for a sub­se­quent visit.</p>
    <p>Be­ing glut­tons, my com­pan­ions and I or­dered the half por­tion (above). We couldn’t fin­ish it.</p>
    <p>A cal­zone is ba­si­cally a pizza that is folded over. It looks like a mam­moth curry puff and the one here is stuffed plumply with cheeses that stretch into long strings when you pull it apart. What you taste first is ri­cotta, which has a slightly grainy tex­ture and is mild enough for most palates.</p>
    <p>Get an ex­tra serv­ing of sauce ($5), which is de­li­cious enough to drink. The acid­ity of toma­toes is a per­fect match for the cheese.</p>

